sentences.english: I pulled up, cash in hand.
sentences.chinese: 我把钱掏了出来，拿在手里。

sentences.english: He took them and laid them in Eponine's hand.
sentences.chinese: 他掏了出来，放在爱潘妮手里。

sentences.english: The man reached again into his pocket for the matches.
sentences.chinese: 他又把手伸到口袋里面去掏火柴。

sentences.english: There were about twenty taels of silver in all.
sentences.chinese: 将怀中带着的二十几两碎银子都掏了出来。

sentences.english: Whenever I hear the word gun, I reach for my culture.
sentences.chinese: 一听到枪这个字，我赶紧掏我的文化。

sentences.english: He will have to cough up ￡15 for that shirt.
sentences.chinese: 要买那衬衫他得掏15英镑。

sentences.english: I reached down to grab it and realized there was no BlackBerry there.
sentences.chinese: 我伸手去掏手机，意识到它并不在那里。

sentences.english: All closing costs and pre-paids will be paid out of pocket at escrow.
sentences.chinese: 所有费用和闭幕前将自掏口袋低收入下午代管。

sentences.english: He bought me a pack of cigarettes, from the bag and pulls out.
sentences.chinese: 他给我买了包烟，从包里掏了出来。

sentences.english: He said, "Mexico will pay for the wall" by reimbursing the United States.
sentences.chinese: 他说，墨西哥会通过补偿美国掏这笔修墙的钱。

sentences.english: They dug a deep hole in the hillside.
sentences.chinese: 他们在山坡上掏了一个深洞。

sentences.english: Blankness, digs out the light from heart.
They always make you pay a deposit on the bidon, and you get it back when the bidon is returned.
sentences.chinese: 他们总是非要你掏油壶的押金，油壶还回去退押金。

sentences.english: 'Abracadabra, ' said the conjuror as he pulled the rabbit from the hat.
sentences.chinese: 魔术师口中念念有词，把兔子从礼帽中掏了出来。
